<h1>On you and your friends' privacy...</h1>
<h2>What information is collected and/or used?</h2>
This application, by default, has access to your public profile and your friend list.
For a detailed look at what information is available through your public profile, 
<a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/reference/login/public-profile-and-friend-list/" target="top">click here</a>.
<br /><br />From your public profile, only your name, user ID, and friend list are used.
<h2>What about my friends' information?</h2>
Other than their displayed name on your friend list, your friends' information isn't accessed through your use of the application.
<h2>How is the collected information used?</h2>
Your name, user ID, and friend list are only used to serve the functions of this application. 
The information will never be sold to or willingly shared with any third parties.
<br /><br />
For more general purpose questions, please visit the <a href="?page=faq">FAQ page</a>.
